column11:
Strategy for solving the problem using ArrayLists: 

Start by creating a for loop with int i = arr.size() which runs for every element in arr. 
Then check if the element at index i == 0 if yes then remove the element. 
return arr at the end. 



Strategy for solving the problem using classic arrays. 

First start by creating a variable S and initialize it to the array length - 1. this will serve as the end index. 
Then create a for loop with int O = 0 which runs for every element in the array. 
If the element at index O == 0 then: 
create an initialize a variable, lets call it A to 0; 
then create a while loop which runs until S-A == 0; 
it adds 1 to A each time it runs. 
This will give us the index of the first non zero number from the right of the array. 
Then create an if statement to check if O is equal to S-A+1 or in other words check if the all the elements after the element at index O have been changed and are all Zeros. 
if this is true then add arr.length to O so as to exit the for loop. 
Then in the else statement for this if statement:
Create an int variable lets call it X and set it to the element at index S-A or the first non 0 from the right. then set that element to 0. 
Then finally set the element on index O to X or the first non zero element from the right. 
Return arr and print in the main method using for loops instead of for:each loops so as to maintain the aesthetics.
